1
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:32,030
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,960
[Episode 3]

3
00:01:37,009 --> 00:01:38,140
We want to talk here.

4
00:01:45,450 --> 00:01:46,320
Go ahead now.

5
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,550
Xiaoyue,

6
00:01:50,940 --> 00:01:53,410
I asked someone to pass on
a message to the Manager, saying

7
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:54,050
that I joined the army.

8
00:01:54,050 --> 00:01:55,110
Didn't he tell you?

9
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,440
What's wrong?

10
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:02,930
The Manager

11
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,300
died.

12
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:06,130
What?

13
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,240
He died?

14
00:02:11,650 --> 00:02:12,710
That night,

15
00:02:12,730 --> 00:02:13,930
in our room,

16
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:17,400
Buns and I were putting up
double happiness papercuts.

17
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,640
Gunfire and artillery
went off outside all of a sudden,

18
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,440
and the streets fell into chaos.

19
00:02:21,530 --> 00:02:22,329
Japanese planes

20
00:02:22,329 --> 00:02:23,980
started dropping bombs.

21
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:26,960
The streets were filled
with fleeing refugees.

22
00:02:27,210 --> 00:02:29,210
Not even knowing
where the bullets came from,

23
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:31,540
people just suddenly fell as they walked.

24
00:02:32,180 --> 00:02:33,400
The Manager, Buns, and I,

25
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,660
we ran outside.

26
00:02:35,050 --> 00:02:35,910
Halfway there,

27
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,240
the Manager said
he hadn't taken the land deed

28
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,700
and insisted on going back.

29
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,460
He said

30
00:02:41,210 --> 00:02:42,490
he was afraid the fire
would burn the house down,

31
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:43,690
ruining everything.

32
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,750
And then?

33
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:50,180
Then a bomb dropped

34
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:52,610
and hit him.

35
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:56,770
That day, the fire raged all night,

36
00:02:57,490 --> 00:02:59,980
turning the whole sky red.

37
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,270
So,

38
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:07,800
our home is

39
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:10,260
gone, too?

40
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:14,510
It's gone.

41
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:17,500
Everything is gone.

42
00:03:23,550 --> 00:03:26,220
I've been looking for you all these days.

43
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,860
In refugee camps, hospitals,

44
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:30,660
-I've been looking for you everywhere.
-I know. I know.

45
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:32,030
I was just afraid you were hit

46
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:33,400
by a stray bullet on the street.

47
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,990
What would I do then?

48
00:03:35,010 --> 00:03:36,900
I know. I know.

49
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:39,020
Stop crying. Don't cry.

50
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,250
You are so timid

51
00:03:42,610 --> 00:03:43,750
and hate pain.

52
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:46,100
Bullets on the battlefield
don't discriminate.

53
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,570
What if you really get wounded?

54
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,150
-I don't want to be this stupid...
-Well...

55
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:54,160
This young lady is your wife, right?

56
00:03:56,220 --> 00:04:00,140
Your man is very brave on the battlefield.

57
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:02,320
He's a good soldier.

58
00:04:03,090 --> 00:04:04,130
What's more,

59
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:05,570
he is disciplined

60
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,160
and follows the rules,

61
00:04:07,210 --> 00:04:08,180
right?

62
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:10,670
Yes.

63
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:14,950
Xiaoyue, don't worry.

64
00:04:14,970 --> 00:04:17,470
I-I'm not the kind of soldier
who charges to the front.

65
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:18,579
I-I hide in the back.

66
00:04:18,579 --> 00:04:19,680
I'm an orderly,

67
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,610
following the commanders.

68
00:04:20,610 --> 00:04:21,240
You know,

69
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:22,170
on the battlefield,

70
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:23,410
commanders are the least likely to die.

71
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:24,430
I just follow them.

72
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,200
I'm really shrewd.

73
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:25,620
Don't worry.

74
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:26,700
I will surely make it back alive.

75
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,020
I promise I will.

76
00:04:28,050 --> 00:04:29,980
I will definitely come back alive.

77
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,400
Okay.

78
00:04:32,430 --> 00:04:34,490
I will definitely make it back alive.

79
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,650
Then try your best to fight the Japanese.

80
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:39,970
I'll wait for you to come back.

81
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:46,010
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

82
00:04:44,580 --> 00:04:45,909
We're so unlucky.

83
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:48,659
God has given us bad luck!

84
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:50,790
Don't believe in fate, sir.

85
00:04:51,190 --> 00:04:53,300
Are you still blaming it on God now?

86
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,040
It's empty talk!

87
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:57,330
Who drove you out of your hometown

88
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,380
and made you unable to farm your own land?

89
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:00,390
And who

90
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:01,860
made you homeless,

91
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:03,490
starving, and suffering?

92
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,430
All of these were

93
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,860
caused by humans!

94
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:07,850
Yes,

95
00:05:08,170 --> 00:05:09,610
the ones who made us starve and suffer

96
00:05:09,610 --> 00:05:10,850
and made us homeless are

97
00:05:10,850 --> 00:05:12,380
the Japanese imperialists

98
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:15,000
and the non-resisting traitors to China!

99
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:17,600
Everyone, let's join hands!

100
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:20,070
Let's bring down our enemy together!

101
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:21,260
Friends,

102
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,330
we must stand together.

103
00:05:23,530 --> 00:05:25,170
We must seek revenge

104
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:27,310
and fight against those

105
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:29,320
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

106
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:29,290
who oppress and exploit us!

107
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,820
We cannot forget
the September 18 Incident!

108
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:34,670
We cannot forget
what happened at the Lugou Bridge!

109
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,710
The Chinese nation is

110
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,400
at its most perilous moment.

111
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:40,860
We must stand united!

112
00:05:41,550 --> 00:05:44,800
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

113
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:48,040
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

114
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:50,870
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

115
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:53,950
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

116
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,620
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

117
00:05:56,510 --> 00:05:58,930
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

118
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:59,260
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

119
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,780
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

120
00:06:01,780 --> 00:06:05,720
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

121
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:05,120
Eliminate the Japanese
and protect the country!

122
00:06:05,210 --> 00:06:06,020
Bravo!

123
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:08,330
Good show!

124
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:11,270
Good show! Bravo!

125
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:13,230
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

126
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:12,410
Nice show!

127
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,330
Bravo!

128
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,690
Bravo!

129
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:19,020
Bravo!

130
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:22,320
Xiaoyue, hurry up and pack your things.

131
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,640
I have to go back.

132
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:26,700
I'll make a special trip
to visit you another day,

133
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:27,460
okay?

134
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:30,580
Xiaoyue. Xiaoyue!

135
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:35,140
You...

136
00:06:35,490 --> 00:06:36,620
have joined the army?

137
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:37,500
Hello, Miss Yu.

138
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:39,650
Let me help you.

139
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:42,050
By the way,

140
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:43,830
what is Miss Yu's plan?

141
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:47,170
Our master plans to retreat to Wuhan.

142
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,070
To Wuhan?

143
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:52,110
Okay. Listen, Xiaoyue.

144
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,180
Just go wherever the Yu family goes.

145
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,680
If they go to Wuhan, you go there as well.

146
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,280
Okay.

147
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,140
Then, when the war is over here,

148
00:06:59,140 --> 00:06:59,990
I'll go find you.

149
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:00,700
Don't worry.

150
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,120
I'm safe following them.

151
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:03,800
But you,
with all the fighting and killing,

152
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,850
make sure you take care of yourself.

153
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:05,650
Do you hear me?

154
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,370
Don't worry. As shrewd as I am,

155
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,600
I'll be fine for sure.

156
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,560
Here's the money I've saved.

157
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:17,560
Take it with you.

158
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,210
Xiaoyue,

159
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:19,020
hurry up,

160
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:20,650
-We need to rush to the next place.
-Hey, I'm a soldier. I have money.

161
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,860
-Why should I t-take it?
-I don't need it. Use it however you want.

162
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:23,650
Xiaoyue.

163
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,250
Xiaoyue!

164
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:40,190
Stop there!

165
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:40,920
Xiaoyue!

166
00:07:41,590 --> 00:07:42,200
Here,

167
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:43,460
take it.

168
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:49,700
Put it on!

169
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,180
Does it look good?

170
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,430
Yes!

171
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:58,570
Wait for me in Wuhan!

172
00:07:58,850 --> 00:07:59,820
Okay!

173
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:08,940
Let's go.

174
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,050
Let's go back.

175
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,020
Let's go.

176
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,730
Any news?

177
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:35,710
Not yet.

178
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:54,920
Brigade Commander, it's time to eat.

179
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:38,010
[Nanjing]

180
00:09:40,190 --> 00:09:41,100
Father,

181
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,040
take a rest and have some tea.

182
00:09:45,690 --> 00:09:46,760
Master!

183
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,200
Madam!

184
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:49,500
We won the battle!

185
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,650
We won!

186
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:53,690
A great victory!

187
00:09:54,050 --> 00:09:55,250
Here you are, Master.

188
00:09:56,090 --> 00:09:57,290
It's a great victory.

189
00:09:57,610 --> 00:09:59,570
[Shanghai News]

190
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:11,930
The Japanese have sent
more troops to the Wusong Estuary.

191
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,220
Well,

192
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:18,580
we haven't heard from Yunkui for so long.

193
00:10:18,580 --> 00:10:19,820
Where is he now?

194
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:24,960
Yujiao.

195
00:10:27,050 --> 00:10:29,380
Military forces have
no constant formation,

196
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,380
just as water has no constant shape.

197
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:34,610
One who adapts
to the enemy's changes to win is

198
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,340
considered formidable.

199
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,630
During wartime,

200
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,300
military mail doesn't get through.

201
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,780
Soldiers have no time to write home.

202
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:49,230
Not to mention
that officers' movements are top secret.

203
00:10:49,530 --> 00:10:50,410
Therefore,

204
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:51,970
don't expect any news

205
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,810
from Yunkui.

206
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:56,230
I know, Father.

207
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:58,670
Look,

208
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:00,210
it's Luodian,

209
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:02,470
Yuepu,

210
00:11:02,990 --> 00:11:03,750
and Baoshan.

211
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:06,810
The fighting along this line
has been quite fierce.

212
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,450
Look,

213
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:09,330
this is a triangular area, right?

214
00:11:09,730 --> 00:11:12,600
But what if the Japanese Army
concentrates its sea, land,

215
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,060
and air forces on one point

216
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:15,290
to attack us?

217
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:18,930
Knowing our firepower is
weaker than theirs,

218
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,270
why did we still deploy

219
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:22,460
a large number of troops here?

220
00:11:22,490 --> 00:11:23,490
It's not worth it.

221
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:24,820
What a misjudgment!

222
00:11:35,930 --> 00:11:36,890
Yujiao.

223
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,040
You are pregnant.

224
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:41,700
Don't think too much.

225
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:44,440
Mrs. Liu.

226
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:45,640
Yes, Master.

227
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,500
Starting tomorrow,

228
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:49,960
you need to add some astragalus

229
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:51,420
to Yujiao's chicken soup.

230
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,720
It invigorates the blood and boosts Qi

231
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,880
as well as Yang energy.

232
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:54,740
But not too much.

233
00:11:54,740 --> 00:11:55,470
Just 6 maces.

234
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:56,240
Six maces.

235
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,840
I still have a hen stewing on the stove.

236
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,010
Oh, my old hen!

237
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,360
Six maces, six maces.

238
00:12:09,140 --> 00:12:09,980
Father.

239
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:11,010
Yujiao,

240
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,920
you are going to be a mother.

241
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:16,140
You must put your mind at ease
and nourish your Qi.

242
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:19,740
Have you tried the calming method

243
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,300
I taught you?

244
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:23,170
Father,

245
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,990
it's not that easy.

246
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:28,970
Ever since the last air raid,

247
00:12:29,050 --> 00:12:31,180
I can't even stand hearing hoofbeats.

248
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,770
Whenever I hear this sound,

249
00:12:32,770 --> 00:12:34,220
it reminds me of Yunkui.

250
00:12:35,450 --> 00:12:37,310
We were all fleeing for our lives.

251
00:12:37,570 --> 00:12:40,170
Yet Yunkui was
desperately charging forward.

252
00:12:40,420 --> 00:12:42,550
It makes me sad just thinking about it.

253
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:44,740
Don't be sad.

254
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:46,640
Relax.

255
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,290
Keep calm.

256
00:12:53,810 --> 00:12:55,860
Father, the alarm is sounding again.

257
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:57,860
Let's hurry to the air raid shelter.

258
00:12:58,410 --> 00:13:00,620
Mrs. Liu! Mrs. Liu!

259
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:02,770
Yi!

260
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:04,940
-Don't panic!
-Yi!

261
00:13:06,830 --> 00:13:08,520
What did I just say?

262
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:13,000
[The Gentleman Is Not a Vessel]

263
00:13:09,950 --> 00:13:13,070
The gentleman is not a vessel.

264
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:16,830
Not a vessel. (Sounds like "relax.")

265
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:17,910
I understand.

266
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,710
Relax, relax.

267
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,470
Don't be upset, no matter what.

268
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:32,940
Yi! Yi!

269
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:35,710
[The Gentleman Is Not a Vessel]

270
00:13:33,740 --> 00:13:35,070
Yi!

271
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:05,070
[The Gentleman Is Not a Vessel]

272
00:14:10,570 --> 00:14:12,170
Hello, this is Zhang Yunkui!

273
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:20,900
Hello?

274
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:21,860
Deputy Division Commander Liao,

275
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:22,770
3 days after 3 days.

276
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:25,180
When exactly
will the 159th Division arrive?

277
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:25,940
Yunkui,

278
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:29,210
the 159th Division ran into trouble
on their way.

279
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:30,530
The enemy has cut off

280
00:14:30,530 --> 00:14:32,590
all contact between Liu Town and you.

281
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:34,500
Currently, the 159th Division is

282
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:36,620
also under immense pressure in Liu Town.

283
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:37,500
But Liu Town is

284
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,900
only about 15 kilometers from here!

285
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:40,590
Our communications have been cut off.

286
00:14:40,590 --> 00:14:42,260
The current situation is unclear.

287
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:44,170
Yunkui, hold out for another 3 days.

288
00:14:44,170 --> 00:14:44,830
Just 3 days.

289
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,450
It'll be on them

290
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:46,570
if they don't arrive in 3 days.

291
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:47,450
At a time like this,

292
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,050
are we still talking about responsibility?

293
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:50,910
Deputy Division Commander Liao!

294
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,140
Our brigade had over 6,000 men,

295
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:54,260
and now there are only 400 left.

296
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:55,690
We really can't hold out much longer.

297
00:14:55,690 --> 00:14:57,020
At this rate, the Japanese Army

298
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:58,650
will break through us sooner or later!

299
00:14:58,650 --> 00:15:00,050
Deputy Division Commander Liao,

300
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:01,320
I request an initiative to retreat.

301
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:03,050
Retreat to Liu Town,
meet the 159th Division,

302
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:04,380
and strike back at them.

303
00:15:04,410 --> 00:15:06,650
The Japanese will definitely think
we are retreating in panic,

304
00:15:06,650 --> 00:15:07,980
underestimate us, and advance rashly.

305
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,380
This way, we can use solid fortifications

306
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:10,290
in Liu Town

307
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:11,500
to stop the Japanese,

308
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,820
attack their advance troops
from both flanks,

309
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:15,220
and catch them off guard.

310
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:19,590
Impossible.

311
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:22,000
Carry out the order right away.

312
00:15:36,340 --> 00:15:37,400
Staff Officer Xie,

313
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:39,250
call Commander Liu
and Commander Feng to a meeting.

314
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:39,980
Understood.

315
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:44,020
The enemy is determined to win,

316
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,980
and our army is determined
to defend to the death.

317
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,950
Unfortunately,
the disparity in weapons is huge,

318
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:55,240
[Faithfulness and Empathy]

319
00:15:49,980 --> 00:15:53,340
and the higher-ups favor a passive,
purely defensive strategy.

320
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:56,290
This time marching to Baijiazhai Town,

321
00:15:57,170 --> 00:15:59,660
the enemy's offensive is stronger,

322
00:15:59,780 --> 00:16:01,510
and the prospect remains unpredictable.

323
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:03,650
Fortunately, all officers
and soldiers of our brigade

324
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:07,100
share the same resolve
to defend Shanghai to the death.

325
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:10,390
If I die,

326
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:12,390
but Shanghai remains safe,

327
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:14,490
my wish will be fulfilled.

328
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:23,060
Father taught me

329
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:26,170
that when loyalty
collides with filial piety,

330
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:29,870
serving the country equals filial piety.

331
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,280
[Faithfulness and Empathy]

332
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:33,200
Therefore, I have no other thoughts
on this battle.

333
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:38,130
I only wish you to take care of yourself

334
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:43,540
and forgive me for not being able
to fulfill my filial duties by your side.

335
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:45,640
Yujiao,

336
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,110
a soldier

337
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:49,100
will write a suicide note

338
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:51,010
before a major battle

339
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:52,780
to express his determination.

340
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:54,380
Don't be sad.

341
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:58,630
Yunkui is a soldier
cultivated by the country.

342
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:03,450
He is a descendant
of the Chinese scholars for 3,000 years.

343
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:06,520
No matter what happens to him this time,

344
00:17:07,339 --> 00:17:09,819
whether he dies or survives,

345
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:13,130
we should all be proud of him.

346
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,680
I will live my life well.

347
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:16,940
And you

348
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,410
must take good care of yourself, too.

349
00:17:20,089 --> 00:17:20,960
Only this way

350
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:24,040
can Yunkui feel at ease.

351
00:17:27,170 --> 00:17:28,470
Don't read the rest.

352
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:30,560
That's all written for you.

353
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:33,840
Father,

354
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:35,550
Yunkui

355
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:37,400
also asked you

356
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:40,370
to name the unborn child.

357
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:41,310
No rush.

358
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:44,670
Let's wait for him to come back

359
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,930
and name the child.

360
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:50,990
Thank you, Father.

361
00:17:56,870 --> 00:17:58,310
Sweet dreams.

362
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:01,140
Sweet dreams.

363
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:35,740
[September 19, 1937, Mid-Autumn Festival]

364
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:12,490
According to the scout,

365
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:13,570
there's only one enemy squadron

366
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:14,690
between Liu Town and us.

367
00:19:14,690 --> 00:19:15,230
Here

368
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:16,050
and here.

369
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:17,900
They happen to grab us by the neck.

370
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:19,800
It's hard for the 159th Division
to come over.

371
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,020
What are you thinking?

372
00:19:21,020 --> 00:19:22,340
With so many Japanese out there now,

373
00:19:22,340 --> 00:19:23,820
the 159th Division can barely survive!

374
00:19:23,820 --> 00:19:25,300
Yet you still expect them to support us?

375
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,100
Brigade Commander,

376
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,330
give an order to retreat.

377
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:28,340
If we don't retreat,

378
00:19:28,340 --> 00:19:29,740
all our men will die here.

379
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:31,310
The Division Commander's order is to hold.

380
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,840
We can't hold out for 3 days.

381
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:34,060
By tomorrow,

382
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,030
400 people will be reduced to 200.

383
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:38,490
By the day after tomorrow,
we'll all be gone.

384
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:41,860
Call the Division Headquarters.

385
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:44,860
Brigade Commander,
there's still a fault in the line.

386
00:19:45,130 --> 00:19:46,010
Brigade Commander,

387
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:47,680
how about we send someone
to the 159th Division?

388
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,880
At least, we can hold on for one more day.

389
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,920
It's too late.

390
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:56,030
Fetch me the horse.

391
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:56,960
Yes, Commander.

392
00:19:57,970 --> 00:19:58,750
I'm going to the Division Headquarters.

393
00:19:58,750 --> 00:19:59,830
Wait for my news.

394
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:11,780
[Emperor Guan Temple]

395
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:18,220
[Emperor Guan Temple]

396
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:10,750
[Nanjing]

397
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:07,350
This is Commander of the 87th Brigade,
Zhang Yunkui.

398
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:08,750
I'm here to report to you.

399
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:11,660
Who asked you to come?

400
00:22:12,910 --> 00:22:15,230
Didn't you order him to hold his ground?

401
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,100
Division Commander, I came on my own.

402
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:20,170
We really can't
miss the opportunity again.

403
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:20,860
The enemy in front will

404
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,100
surely underestimate us
and advance rashly.

405
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,250
I can pretend to retreat,

406
00:22:23,250 --> 00:22:24,100
lure the enemy in deep,

407
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,010
and then strike back,

408
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:26,260
completely wiping them out.

409
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:28,010
But if we hold our ground to the death,

410
00:22:28,010 --> 00:22:29,300
I'm afraid we'll be annihilated

411
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:30,730
even before the reinforcements arrive.

412
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:31,690
Zhang Yunkui,

413
00:22:32,010 --> 00:22:33,210
this is a military order
from the war zone.

414
00:22:33,210 --> 00:22:35,300
It's not your place
to make random remarks.

415
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,210
Given your absence from your post
without permission,

416
00:22:37,210 --> 00:22:39,070
I can shoot you to death right now.

417
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:42,970
I used to be your chief of staff.

418
00:22:42,970 --> 00:22:44,450
Now I'm your brigade commander.

419
00:22:44,450 --> 00:22:45,580
You know what kind of person I am.

420
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:46,580
I'm not doing this for myself.

421
00:22:46,580 --> 00:22:47,490
I'm doing this for our army,

422
00:22:47,490 --> 00:22:48,490
for our division.

423
00:22:48,580 --> 00:22:50,970
You are neither the Division Commander
nor the Army Commander.

424
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:54,500
You should go back and execute
the military order immediately.

425
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:03,020
Yunkui.

426
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:07,830
Division Commander,

427
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,160
I'm not afraid of death,

428
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:11,800
but we really can't afford
to miss our chance in battle again!

429
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,260
So I implore you to allow me

430
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,060
to go to Liu Town

431
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:15,860
and support the 159th Division.

432
00:23:35,430 --> 00:23:37,450
Yunkui, you may go back first.

433
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,280
I will report to the higher-ups.

434
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:40,450
If you don't get a call

435
00:23:40,450 --> 00:23:41,710
by 10 o'clock tonight,

436
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:42,910
just go ahead.

437
00:23:45,010 --> 00:23:45,710
Yes!

438
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:55,810
Division Commander.

439
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:56,340
Division Commander.

440
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:57,340
What do you think?

441
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:35,150
[Nanjing Public Air-Raid Shelter]

442
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,660
A little mouse climbs the lampstand

443
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:37,720
and can't get down.

444
00:25:11,410 --> 00:25:14,250
-Mom, I'm scared.
-Don't be afraid, baby.

445
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,210
I'm here with you. Don't be scared.

446
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:18,700
There were more than 30 planes today,

447
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:20,090
all flying from Shanghai.

448
00:25:20,090 --> 00:25:21,300
They bombed our radio station,

449
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:22,030
water plant,

450
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:23,350
and military departments.

451
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:25,150
Who said they only bombed these?

452
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,890
My cousin lived on Fuxi Street.

453
00:25:26,930 --> 00:25:27,860
This afternoon,

454
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:30,490
2 out of 3 courtyards
of his house were destroyed.

455
00:25:30,490 --> 00:25:32,520
My uncle, aunt, and cousin were

456
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:33,820
all bombed to death.

457
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:35,100
The Japanese

458
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:37,830
suffered great losses in Shanghai.

459
00:25:37,950 --> 00:25:39,020
It was a revenge.

460
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,920
They took revenge on civilians.

461
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:44,670
This only shows how incapable and cowardly

462
00:25:44,900 --> 00:25:45,960
they are!

463
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:46,850
Yes,

464
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,140
the old gentleman has got a point.

465
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:50,150
Yes, that makes sense!

466
00:25:50,210 --> 00:25:50,930
They're cowardly.

467
00:25:50,930 --> 00:25:54,190
He who God wishes to destroy
will first be driven out of his mind.

468
00:25:54,190 --> 00:25:55,640
They even spoke wildly,

469
00:25:55,780 --> 00:25:58,620
saying they'd occupy China in 3 months!

470
00:25:58,970 --> 00:26:01,140
In their dreams!

471
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:02,760
They were talking nonsense!

472
00:26:04,130 --> 00:26:05,380
Drive them all out!

473
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:05,970
That's insane.

474
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:06,970
Japanese devils!

475
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:09,130
These Japanese are so vicious.

476
00:26:09,130 --> 00:26:09,820
Really.

477
00:26:09,820 --> 00:26:10,970
Trapped here,

478
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:13,030
we can't even see the moon on the 15th.

479
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,280
Will we be crushed

480
00:26:20,310 --> 00:26:22,690
and hit by bombs?

481
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:23,780
No, it won't happen.

482
00:26:23,780 --> 00:26:25,860
-Is it really going to collapse?
-Mom, look.

483
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:28,210
The moon is so round.

484
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:30,790
Yes,

485
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,210
it's big and round,

486
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,220
right?

487
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:46,770
Today is August 15th.

488
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:48,250
I have a box of mooncakes here.

489
00:26:48,250 --> 00:26:49,970
Let's share them and have a taste.

490
00:26:49,970 --> 00:26:51,990
Yes, I'll treat everyone to tangyuan, too.

491
00:26:51,990 --> 00:26:54,040
I'll treat everyone to wontons.

492
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:55,970
Help me distribute them to everyone.

493
00:26:55,970 --> 00:26:57,240
Have a mooncake, please.

494
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,370
Give them to everyone else.

495
00:26:58,370 --> 00:26:59,450
Okay. Thank you, thank you.

496
00:26:59,450 --> 00:27:01,250
Do you guys want some mooncakes?

497
00:27:01,490 --> 00:27:02,880
Yes, thank you.

498
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:28,780
[Wuhan]

499
00:27:22,220 --> 00:27:23,840
Last year's Mid-Autumn Festival,

500
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:26,570
Zuliang, many of our classmates, and I

501
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,770
enjoyed the moon together at the Bund.

502
00:27:30,770 --> 00:27:33,230
I wonder if Zuliang
has any mooncakes to eat.

503
00:27:34,460 --> 00:27:36,500
I wonder where Wanfu is.

504
00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:41,060
Does he have any mooncakes to eat?

505
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,030
Silly girl,

506
00:27:43,780 --> 00:27:47,080
don't you always praise Wanfu
for being smart

507
00:27:47,110 --> 00:27:48,590
and sharp-witted?

508
00:27:49,170 --> 00:27:51,210
He will definitely be safe.

509
00:27:59,140 --> 00:28:01,380
To Division Commander Sun Huaiyi.

510
00:28:02,230 --> 00:28:05,450
[Loyalty and Virtue Endure Forever]

511
00:28:02,740 --> 00:28:05,850
My 6,000 soldiers have all sacrificed.

512
00:28:06,730 --> 00:28:08,270
If the ground is held,

513
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:10,860
I shall survive to see you

514
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,680
and apologize for my offense.

515
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:15,560
If the ground is lost,

516
00:28:16,150 --> 00:28:17,280
I will die in battle,

517
00:28:17,370 --> 00:28:19,230
and my body
will be left in the wilderness.

518
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:21,250
One day, after the victory of the war,

519
00:28:21,250 --> 00:28:22,850
you will be a famous general.

520
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:24,450
When you drive through Shanghai,

521
00:28:24,450 --> 00:28:26,690
if you hear the wind blowing
through the pines like the sea waves,

522
00:28:26,690 --> 00:28:28,490
that will be me coming to see you.

523
00:28:29,210 --> 00:28:31,010
The 6,000 lonely souls behind me

524
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:34,290
will also rest in peace in the underworld.

525
00:28:41,630 --> 00:28:42,600
Brigade Commander,

526
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,620
I made some food for you.

527
00:28:51,070 --> 00:28:53,130
It's the Mid-Autumn Festival today.

528
00:28:58,210 --> 00:28:59,050
Erbao.

529
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:05,160
Did you just say today is
the Mid-Autumn Festival?

530
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:06,910
Look.

531
00:29:22,570 --> 00:29:23,370
A mooncake.

532
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,330
I made it.

533
00:29:26,930 --> 00:29:27,960
Do our men all have some?

534
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,000
They all do.

535
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:30,660
It's a major festival,

536
00:29:30,770 --> 00:29:32,830
so I made some for the men to hold onto.

537
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:36,910
Don't split it. Don't.

538
00:29:36,970 --> 00:29:38,540
I made this with water caltrops.

539
00:29:38,540 --> 00:29:40,200
It'll shatter if you break it.

540
00:29:40,910 --> 00:29:42,300
C-Catch the crumbs.

541
00:29:52,890 --> 00:29:53,740
Is it good?

542
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:55,660
It's delicious.

543
00:29:57,230 --> 00:30:00,430
How did you think
of using water caltrops for the filling?

544
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:02,440
We have nothing left, right?

545
00:30:02,470 --> 00:30:03,860
I saw the pond next to our position was

546
00:30:03,860 --> 00:30:05,580
awash with water caltrops.

547
00:30:05,610 --> 00:30:06,270
So I wondered

548
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:08,260
if I could mash these water caltrops
and shape them

549
00:30:08,260 --> 00:30:09,190
into mooncakes.

550
00:30:09,210 --> 00:30:11,070
I didn't expect it to really work.

551
00:30:11,090 --> 00:30:12,280
It was just too rushed.

552
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:14,560
I spent ages on this water caltrop dough.

553
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:16,610
You know, I formed the shape

554
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:19,470
of this mooncake
with a fired artillery shell.

555
00:30:19,700 --> 00:30:20,610
You have no idea.

556
00:30:20,610 --> 00:30:21,860
Those fired artillery shells are

557
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:23,900
either broken or flat.

558
00:30:24,010 --> 00:30:24,970
It wasn't easy for me

559
00:30:24,970 --> 00:30:26,250
to find a round one.

560
00:30:26,280 --> 00:30:27,590
How amazing I am!

561
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:29,800
Anyway, when we get to Shanghai,

562
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:31,520
I'll make you a real mooncake

563
00:30:31,550 --> 00:30:32,950
with date paste filling.

564
00:30:33,170 --> 00:30:36,370
I assure you, it will taste
better than Guan Sheng Yuan's.

565
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:41,270
Water, have some water.

566
00:30:45,450 --> 00:30:46,580
Brigade Commander,

567
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:48,480
I have another good thing here.

568
00:30:52,310 --> 00:30:53,440
Where did you get it?

569
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:55,540
Weren't we digging trenches?

570
00:30:55,540 --> 00:30:57,210
We tore down 2 houses on the edge of town

571
00:30:57,210 --> 00:31:00,010
and found several jars of it
buried under the wall.

572
00:31:00,790 --> 00:31:02,120
You grab a mug, too.

573
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:14,900
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

574
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:18,020
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival, Commander.

575
00:31:21,170 --> 00:31:21,960
Good wine.

576
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,430
Let's go to the frontline.

577
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,300
Come here, Erbao,

578
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:27,940
help me take off my boots.

579
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,620
How did you tie these puttees?

580
00:31:52,690 --> 00:31:53,840
I don't know how to tie properly.

581
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:56,260
Three wraps clockwise,
three wraps counterclockwise,

582
00:31:56,260 --> 00:31:57,900
the scale layers pressed flat
with 3 clockwise wraps,

583
00:31:57,900 --> 00:32:00,300
and the end of the rope
tucked into the seam.

584
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:02,990
Tie them over again.

585
00:32:06,540 --> 00:32:07,470
Erbao.

586
00:32:08,690 --> 00:32:09,570
The wine we just tasted

587
00:32:09,570 --> 00:32:11,370
should be Lanlingxiang, right?

588
00:32:11,410 --> 00:32:12,430
Brigade Commander,

589
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:13,960
you know so much about wine!

590
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:15,680
That is Lanling Amber.

591
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:17,940
Have you heard a poem by Li Bai?

592
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:20,430
"Lanling's fine wine smells like tulips,

593
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,900
amber light glimmering in the jade cup."

594
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,580
It's talking about this wine.

595
00:32:24,660 --> 00:32:26,490
It's "amber light glimmering
in the jade bowl."

596
00:32:26,490 --> 00:32:27,540
You even know Li Bai?

597
00:32:27,540 --> 00:32:29,210
This is the wine from our hometown.

598
00:32:29,210 --> 00:32:31,390
Everyone in our hometown knows Li Bai.

599
00:32:31,620 --> 00:32:32,950
Isn't it so coincidental?

600
00:32:32,950 --> 00:32:33,820
I actually dug out

601
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:35,510
the wine from our hometown here.

602
00:32:35,510 --> 00:32:36,810
This is destiny.

603
00:32:37,140 --> 00:32:38,540
The one we just drank is

604
00:32:38,820 --> 00:32:41,330
the Xun family's Lanling Amber.

605
00:32:41,430 --> 00:32:42,560
The Wang family's is

606
00:32:42,690 --> 00:32:44,520
called Lanling Drunk.

607
00:32:44,620 --> 00:32:45,650
The one from the Meng family's mansion is

608
00:32:45,650 --> 00:32:47,260
called Lanling Tulip.

609
00:32:48,380 --> 00:32:51,170
With just one poem from Li Bai,

610
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,660
the people in our hometown

611
00:32:52,690 --> 00:32:54,860
have had something to live on
for generations.

612
00:32:54,860 --> 00:32:56,610
We have good wine in our hometown, too.

613
00:32:56,610 --> 00:32:57,400
It's just

614
00:32:57,430 --> 00:32:58,570
that it came out late

615
00:32:58,590 --> 00:33:00,690
and didn't catch
the Poetry Immortal's eye.

616
00:33:00,690 --> 00:33:03,120
Brigade Commander,
you can also compose a poem.

617
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,170
Are you done tying?

618
00:33:04,170 --> 00:33:04,920
Almost.

619
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:07,680
It seems tighter than before.

620
00:33:16,670 --> 00:33:17,560
Let me check.

621
00:33:17,620 --> 00:33:18,170
It's improper.

622
00:33:18,170 --> 00:33:18,830
Attention.

623
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:25,270
Align this.

624
00:33:27,140 --> 00:33:28,270
Then tie it in the middle

625
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:29,460
tightly.

626
00:33:30,380 --> 00:33:31,900
And tuck it into the seam.

627
00:33:32,650 --> 00:33:33,550
And this leg.

628
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:38,470
Done.

629
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:40,670
Go to the front line.

630
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:52,550
Here.

631
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:54,020
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

632
00:33:54,020 --> 00:33:55,280
Thank you, Commander.

633
00:33:56,270 --> 00:33:57,000
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

634
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,140
We even have mooncakes to eat.

635
00:33:58,140 --> 00:33:58,860
Not bad.

636
00:33:58,890 --> 00:34:00,290
We have mooncakes to eat.

637
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:01,760
Thank you.

638
00:34:03,610 --> 00:34:05,350
Have one. Take it.

639
00:34:05,610 --> 00:34:07,030
It's water caltrop filling.

640
00:34:07,030 --> 00:34:08,630
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

641
00:34:08,710 --> 00:34:09,370
Here.

642
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:10,560
Have a mooncake.

643
00:34:21,090 --> 00:34:21,900
Thank you for your hard work.

644
00:34:21,900 --> 00:34:22,679
Thank you, Commander.

645
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:23,810
You've worked hard.

646
00:34:25,409 --> 00:34:27,360
Blindy, sing a song

647
00:34:27,389 --> 00:34:28,520
to lighten the mood.

648
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,199
Good idea.

649
00:34:58,900 --> 00:34:59,690
Brigade Commander.

650
00:34:59,690 --> 00:35:00,820
Brigade Commander.

651
00:35:05,490 --> 00:35:06,270
Brigade Commander.

652
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:07,400
Brigade Commander.

653
00:35:18,050 --> 00:35:21,040
I'm Liu Yishou from Shanxi.

654
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:23,450
Today, I'll sing a Shanxi folk song
for everyone.

655
00:35:23,450 --> 00:35:24,180
How about it?

656
00:35:24,220 --> 00:35:25,490
Good!

657
00:35:25,820 --> 00:35:29,480
♪ A stretch of willow trees on the beach ♪

658
00:35:29,570 --> 00:35:33,180
♪ Turns yellow leaf by leaf ♪

659
00:35:33,340 --> 00:35:38,530
♪ Clusters of sweet dates ♪

660
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:42,130
♪ So red, so red ♪

661
00:35:42,570 --> 00:35:45,740
♪ Bowls of apricot blossom wine ♪

662
00:35:46,010 --> 00:35:49,390
♪ Mellow with every sip ♪

663
00:35:49,740 --> 00:35:54,640
♪ Jars of aged vinegar ♪

664
00:35:55,340 --> 00:35:58,820
♪ It's sour enough to knock me out ♪

665
00:35:58,820 --> 00:36:00,660
Bravo! Bravo!

666
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:01,940
Thank you for the support.

667
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,030
I'm flattered.

668
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:03,930
Bravo!

669
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:04,990
Brigade Commander.

670
00:36:04,990 --> 00:36:06,070
Stand up!

671
00:36:06,770 --> 00:36:07,790
Salute!

672
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:11,100
At ease!

673
00:36:11,250 --> 00:36:12,580
Sit down. Keep singing.

674
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:14,590
Go on!

675
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:17,800
Sit down.

676
00:36:19,820 --> 00:36:21,780
You were singing so well just now.

677
00:36:22,050 --> 00:36:23,410
Why did you stop?

678
00:36:23,490 --> 00:36:24,810
Well, since the Brigade Commander is here,

679
00:36:24,810 --> 00:36:26,460
how about we have the Commander
sing a song?

680
00:36:26,460 --> 00:36:26,920
Brilliant!

681
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:27,410
Commander, sing a song!

682
00:36:27,410 --> 00:36:28,010
Nice!

683
00:36:28,010 --> 00:36:28,610
Commander, sing a song!

684
00:36:28,610 --> 00:36:29,910
Sing one! Sing one!

685
00:36:29,970 --> 00:36:33,240
Sing one! Sing one! Sing one!

686
00:36:33,300 --> 00:36:35,860
Sing one! Sing one! Sing one!

687
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:38,700
Sing one! Sing one! Sing one!

688
00:36:38,700 --> 00:36:40,410
Sing one! Sing one!

689
00:36:40,410 --> 00:36:42,180
Great!

690
00:36:45,860 --> 00:36:47,860
I couldn't sing when I was in school.

691
00:36:48,260 --> 00:36:49,500
But influenced by my father,

692
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:52,170
I can recite a bit of literature.

693
00:36:52,490 --> 00:36:53,450
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

694
00:36:53,450 --> 00:36:55,680
I'll recite a piece
from the "Water Melody"

695
00:36:55,680 --> 00:36:56,600
by Su Shi.

696
00:36:56,660 --> 00:36:57,160
Is that good?

697
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,080
Good!

698
00:37:00,210 --> 00:37:01,660
Don't laugh at me.

699
00:37:05,780 --> 00:37:10,380
♪ When will the moon be
clear and bright? ♪

700
00:37:11,450 --> 00:37:15,260
♪ With a cup of wine in my hand,
I enquire the sky ♪

701
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:20,660
♪ I wonder what time it would be ♪

702
00:37:21,150 --> 00:37:25,500
♪ In the palace on high tonight ♪

703
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:31,060
♪ I'd like to ride the wind to fly home ♪

704
00:37:31,870 --> 00:37:36,480
♪ Yet I fear the crystalline palace ♪

705
00:37:37,310 --> 00:37:42,760
♪ Would be too high and cold for me ♪

706
00:37:57,680 --> 00:37:58,240
Bravo!

707
00:37:58,270 --> 00:37:59,840
Bravo! Bravo!

708
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:00,780
Amazing!

709
00:38:01,940 --> 00:38:03,210
Bravo!

710
00:38:04,380 --> 00:38:05,430
Wu Youcai,

711
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:07,830
you wear glasses, looking quite educated.

712
00:38:07,830 --> 00:38:08,980
You go sing a song.

713
00:38:10,730 --> 00:38:12,170
I'm not much of a singer either.

714
00:38:12,170 --> 00:38:13,560
I'm from Rehe.

715
00:38:13,730 --> 00:38:17,130
Then let me sing a local opera for you.

716
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:23,430
♪ On the Mid-Autumn Festival in August ♪

717
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:24,780
Erbao.

718
00:38:27,310 --> 00:38:29,390
Is there a problem with my singing?

719
00:38:29,420 --> 00:38:30,230
Yes.

720
00:38:30,590 --> 00:38:32,570
It's awful and hard to understand.

721
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:39,970
♪ I, the errand boy, am away from home ♪

722
00:38:40,410 --> 00:38:46,900
♪ Always having three things
I can't return for ♪

723
00:38:49,220 --> 00:38:52,010
♪ First thing ♪

724
00:38:53,510 --> 00:39:03,150
♪ Can't take good care of my parents ♪

725
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:06,180
♪ Second thing ♪

726
00:39:07,090 --> 00:39:12,000
♪ Can't keep my wife ♪

727
00:39:13,010 --> 00:39:17,970
♪ Company ♪

728
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:21,740
♪ Third thing ♪

729
00:39:22,210 --> 00:39:26,130
♪ I fell ill ♪

730
00:39:30,790 --> 00:39:33,300
♪ Third thing ♪

731
00:39:33,890 --> 00:39:41,660
♪ I fell ill at some merchant's inn ♪

732
00:39:57,360 --> 00:39:58,360
How is the radio?

733
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,240
Brigade Commander,
the electron tube is broken.

734
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:01,470
We can't fix it without parts,

735
00:40:01,470 --> 00:40:03,670
and the telephone line was also bombed.

736
00:40:11,540 --> 00:40:12,430
It's too late.

737
00:40:12,460 --> 00:40:13,650
I must go to Liu Town.

738
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:14,770
Organize a reinforced platoon

739
00:40:14,770 --> 00:40:15,790
and have them set off in 2 hours.

740
00:40:15,790 --> 00:40:17,860
Brigade Commander,
you need to stay in command here.

741
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:18,720
Please let me go.

742
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:19,350
I'll go.

743
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:20,490
Don't fight me for it.

744
00:40:20,490 --> 00:40:21,370
I am the commanding officer.

745
00:40:21,370 --> 00:40:22,120
If anyone can go

746
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:24,320
bring back reinforcements, that's me.

747
00:40:29,450 --> 00:40:30,220
All my men!

748
00:40:30,370 --> 00:40:31,330
Yes, Commander!

749
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:33,460
The battle has come to this point.

750
00:40:33,460 --> 00:40:34,730
As you all can see,

751
00:40:34,970 --> 00:40:36,780
I've got no one else to use now.

752
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,770
Marching to Liu Town with me

753
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,240
means only one thing—

754
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:41,750
death.

755
00:40:42,540 --> 00:40:43,500
I know

756
00:40:43,980 --> 00:40:46,110
some of you were conscripted by force.

757
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:48,190
You are not real soldiers.

758
00:40:49,010 --> 00:40:51,010
You haven't received formal training

759
00:40:51,010 --> 00:40:52,820
and don't know how to fight in battle.

760
00:40:52,820 --> 00:40:53,670
Therefore,

761
00:40:54,090 --> 00:40:56,450
you don't have to die with us.

762
00:40:56,630 --> 00:40:58,030
If anyone wants to leave,

763
00:40:58,700 --> 00:40:59,840
I won't stop them.

764
00:41:00,260 --> 00:41:01,320
Just drop your gear

765
00:41:01,930 --> 00:41:02,760
and leave.

766
00:41:13,330 --> 00:41:14,100
Blindy.

767
00:41:15,250 --> 00:41:16,100
Kong Erbao!

768
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:17,710
Yes!

769
00:41:20,130 --> 00:41:22,020
I forced you to stay

770
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:23,600
and watch us die

771
00:41:24,070 --> 00:41:25,350
for one purpose only.

772
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,550
I want to prove

773
00:41:26,790 --> 00:41:28,250
that Chinese soldiers are

774
00:41:28,730 --> 00:41:29,710
competent!

775
00:41:32,260 --> 00:41:33,660
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

776
00:41:33,660 --> 00:41:35,280
You used every method you could think of

777
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:36,530
to make mooncakes

778
00:41:36,620 --> 00:41:37,950
for all of our soldiers.

779
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:39,450
We ate the mooncakes,

780
00:41:39,930 --> 00:41:40,990
looked at the moon,

781
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:42,490
and felt happy!

782
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:44,460
So all of us

783
00:41:44,990 --> 00:41:45,990
want to thank you.

784
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:48,170
Kong Erbao,

785
00:41:48,450 --> 00:41:50,410
you are also worthy of the name

786
00:41:51,380 --> 00:41:52,230
of "Chinese."

787
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:56,110
Pour wine for everyone later,

788
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:57,330
and you can leave.

789
00:41:57,700 --> 00:41:58,990
Go find your fiancée.

790
00:41:59,380 --> 00:42:00,590
But if all of us

791
00:42:00,620 --> 00:42:01,420
die in battle,

792
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,150
and you survive,

793
00:42:04,190 --> 00:42:05,850
I'd like to ask you for a favor.

794
00:42:06,580 --> 00:42:08,710
You must make sure
the men of the 87th Brigade are

795
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:10,230
remembered with honor.

796
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:11,610
Understand?

797
00:42:11,840 --> 00:42:13,170
Understood!

798
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:14,120
Pour the wine.

799
00:42:14,330 --> 00:42:15,780
Yes, Commander!

800
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:34,300
I'll entrust

801
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:36,850
the position to you two.

802
00:42:37,070 --> 00:42:38,860
Please rest assured, Brigade Commander.

803
00:42:38,860 --> 00:42:40,670
As long as I'm here, the position stands.

804
00:42:40,670 --> 00:42:42,060
I am a soldier.

805
00:42:42,500 --> 00:42:44,360
My uniform is my coffin.

806
00:42:50,390 --> 00:42:51,720
The Brigade Commander said

807
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:53,040
it means only one thing—

808
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:53,990
death.

809
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:56,210
Then let it be.

810
00:43:00,290 --> 00:43:01,060
All my men!

811
00:43:01,340 --> 00:43:02,380
Yes!
